commitResults.messageBody: Add Use Case 1-4 in Developer Guide

Used Assisted refactoring to refactor the Address class into Location.

Location makes more sense in our target audience context since the
training location of the client is stored rather than the client's
address.

Labels in FXML elements are renamed to trainingLocation instead of just
location. The change in naming specifically in FXML is because
`location` is a reserved keyword in FXML.

Refer to this S/O discussion on the error
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/56247046/javafx-java-lang-illegalargumentexception-can-not-set-javafx-scene-control-labe

commitResults.messageBody: Update otsched date to be LocalDate instead of string

Use java.time.DayOfWeek instead of creating a new enumeration class for
DayOfWeek.

Purpose: Abstract all functions that interacts with LocalDate into a
single class

In ViewCommand, abstract some logic of execute function to individual
private method. Reduce the complexity of execute function.

In LocalDateUtils, add toString method to convert LocalDate objects to
String in "dd/MM/yy". The method functionality was formerly from
getDateString in OneTimeSchedule.

Add dayToFind and dateToFind variables to
ScheduleContainsKeywordPredicate in order to filter the person list
according to the extension.

The above change allows the application to display the search term the
user actually input.

The above change allows ViewCommand functionality to look for timings
based on the extension's search definition.

Also modified ViewCommandTest to reflect changes.
Test cases for functionality of extension for ViewCommand.

Add lines relevant to the changes made for date stored in
OneTimeSchedule.

ViewCommand now displays the index of the person in the message.

isValidDate method is moved to LocalDateUtils.

Regex for date is also modularized similar to DayOfWeek in
DayOfWeekUtils.
